		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If you really want to work with the NES I would personally suggest getting into modding it. I started back when I was 13 and it actually spurred my interest in computers. I'm actually writing a 6502 assembler at the moment so you could say I've learned something about the NES since then.
<br />
<br />I don't want it to be a shameless promotion of my site, but I run <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesmods.com">http://nesmods.com</a><!-- m -->. I've got some tutorials on modding and a few resources. If you wanna give that a shot I wouldn't mind helping you out.

		

